'''''Gens des nuages''''' is a [[travel journal]] written in [[French language|French]] by [[France|French]] [[Nobel Prize in Literature|Nobel laureate]] [[J. M. G. Le Cl<U+00E9>zio]] and his wife J<U+00E9>mia.

==Title of book in English==
''Gens des nuages'' could be translated as meaning ''The Cloud People''

== Purpose==
It was written during a trip to [[Sahara]] and published in 1990.
==J<U+00E9>mia Le Cl<U+00E9>zio==
J<U+00E9>mia is a [[Sahrawi people|Sahrawi]] and her ancestors were [[nomad]] who lived in the desert area. After her grand mother left her country, she never visited the place before the trip.

